(292, 33, 'Transformable Dining System', 'After gaining an understanding of the balcony context in Palestine and conducting interviews with target users, the project introduces a versatile, transformable table. The design adapts to the user’s needs at different times and for various functions. The table can expand and contract as required, and its top surface doubles as a tray, making it easier to transfer plates between the kitchen and the balcony.', 'Furniture', '', NULL, 0.00, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'approved', NULL, '2026-01-08 11:11:05', 194, '2025-12-27 14:39:14', '2026-02-17 19:26:28', 17),
(293, 185, 'Imtinan side table 50 x 50 x 45cm.', 'The top and the bottom of the table meet in a star shaped Mohogany in-slot drilled into 1.5cm disks that level the top of the table. The star is an Islamic reference to the concept of the \"Seal of the Prophets\" (Khatam al-Anbiya), prophet Muhammad peace be upon him.', 'Furniture', '', NULL, 0.00, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'approved', NULL, '2026-01-08 11:11:05', 194, '2025-12-28 06:21:29', '2026-02-10 02:00:22', 7),
(294, 185, 'Imtinan high table 50 x 50 x 80cm.', 'Each leg is 3 stems steamed and twisted together using a steamer, PVA, wood offcuts, vice and G-clamps. The same principle is used for the support in between. The structure puts together the legs and support using Sapele Mahogany fittings. They remark Islamic geometrical art with an octagonal angle and Jasmin flowers referencing Hebron’s floral embroideries. The fittings are proportionate to the thickness of the twisted legs and the endurance of the material.', 'Furniture', '', NULL, 0.00, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'approved', NULL, '2026-01-08 11:11:05', 194, '2025-12-28 06:21:29', '2026-02-07 07:25:14', 7),
